                h3 Welcome back, Horror Friends,
                p Today I have an update I'd like to share about the future of Video Horror Stats as a site. Some bad some good. First, I'll begin with the more unfortunate news:
                p <strong>Video Horror Stats will receive one final update, containing basic styling changes and some mobile compatibility - but weapons will not be out.</strong>
                p After this update comes out I will be sunsetting the project in the following months up until the domain expires on <strong>July 6th, 2023</strong>. I do not plan to renew it. One might ask why I'm doing this? Well, simply put I'm making the decision to step away from Video Horror Society as a whole. I've had a lot of fun and joy from this game, and I think Hellbent hit the nail on the head when it comes to a competitively balanced asymmetrical title. The game designer in me gets butterflies in my stomach when I think about the thought put into the gameplay. But unfortunately, things are a little too good to be true.
                p Hellbent has been on somewhat of a streak of bad luck recently. Whether it be consistent backpedaling around supporting a specific former Rewinder who hurt many community members, had prior relationships with minors, and situations involving sexual harassment on their part all came to light or straight up art theft with no credit or monetary compensation to the original artist, it's a little too much for me to want to support Hellbent much anymore.
